This paper discusses the use of word embeddings in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also explores bias metrics and their statistical properties, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the ethical concerns surrounding biased embeddings may fall under the category of cyber ethics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
